Two tourists, a German and a Swiss national, lost their
lives on Saturday while an unknown number sustained injuries after their tour
vehicle skidded and rolled over in Maasai Mara. Confirming the incident, Maasai Mara Chief Park warden Stephen
ole Mining told Citizen Digital, that the injured persons have been airlifted
to Nairobi for treatment while the bodies of the deceased persons have likewise
been ferried to Lee Funeral Home.  He also warned drivers to be careful as they navigate the
park's roads while noting that he has informed the family of the deceased persons of their demise.